The paper focuses on program understanding, debugging, and analysis, which are all related to software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also presents an algorithm that maps functions to a vector space, which involves techniques from programming languages (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of neural networks for training the function embeddings also suggests an application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper applies the func2vec algorithm to mining error-handling specifications in file systems and drivers, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
